HEADWORD: Plumbago
<hw>Plum*ba"go</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., from <ets>plumbum</ets>
lead.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Graphite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of herbaceous plants with
pretty salver-shaped corollas, usually blue or violet;
leadwort.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plumbeous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Plumbean</ent>⟦br⟧
